              Claude Commander (cc) -- Keyboard Help

  NAVIGATION
    Up/Down ......... move cursor          Tab ........... switch panel
    PgUp/PgDn ....... page                 Home/End ...... top / bottom
    Enter ........... open dir / run       Backspace ..... parent dir
    Insert .......... tag / untag entry

  FUNCTION KEYS
    F1 .. this help          F3 .. view          F4 .. edit (CCEDIT)
    F5 .. copy*              F6 .. move*          F7 .. make dir
    F8 .. delete             F9 .. menu           F10 . quit
    *F5/F6 copy/move to the OTHER panel; the dialog lets you rename in
     flight. Shift-F6 renames the file in place (same folder).
    F9 / menu bar: the top row shows a pull-down menu bar (Files / Commands /
     Options). Press F9 to drop the current menu down; Left/Right switch menus,
     Up/Down pick an item, Enter runs it, Esc closes. (The classic single
     pop-up menu is available instead in the CCPOP.COM build.)
    Alt-F1/F2 ....... change drive (left / right panel)
    Alt-F5 .......... pack tagged/cursor into an archive (other panel);
                      tagged folders are packed recursively
    Alt-F7 .......... find files by name (CCFIND)
    Alt-F8 .......... search file contents / grep (CCGREP)
    Alt-F9 .......... extract a whole archive to the other panel
    Alt-F10 ......... directory-tree browser: a full-screen list of every
                      sub-folder under the active panel's path. Up/Dn/PgUp/
                      PgDn/Home/End move; Enter jumps the panel into the
                      highlighted folder; Esc closes without changing.

  VIEWERS (the [view] map in cc.ini selects a viewer per extension)
    F3 on a mapped file runs "<viewer> <file>"; unmapped files use the
    built-in text pager. e.g.  [view]  gif = CCIMG
    Built-in pager: Up/Dn/PgUp/PgDn/Home/End scroll; press H to toggle
    between TEXT and a built-in HEX dump (offset / 16 bytes / ASCII) of the
    same file -- no external program; Esc or F3 quits.
    Shipped viewers: CCIMG (bmp/pcx/gif, VGA mode 13h) and CCWAV (PCM
    .wav via the Sound Blaster). Press a key / ESC to return to cc.

  ARCHIVES (the [open] map in cc.ini selects a packer per extension)
    Enter on a .zip . browse it like a folder, INCLUDING sub-folders
                      (Enter a folder to descend, ".." to go back up, Backspace
                      to leave at the top). F5 extracts the cursor member to the
                      other panel (sub-path preserved). With the OTHER panel
                      inside a .zip, F5 ADDS the tagged/cursor files (folders
                      recurse) into that archive.
    Enter on a .d64 . browse a C64 1541 disk image; F5 extracts a file
                      as <name>.PRG; Alt-F9 extracts every file.
    Enter on a .t64 . browse a C64 tape archive; F5 / Alt-F9 extract
                      entries as <name>.PRG (load address restored).
    Enter on a .arj . browse an ARJ archive; F5 / Alt-F9 extract STORED
                      members (compressed members are listed, not yet decoded).
    Enter on a .rar . browse a RAR 4.x archive; F5 / Alt-F9 extract STORED
                      members (RAR compression is proprietary -- browse-first).

  DISPLAY / SELECT
    Ctrl-F1..F4 ..... sort by name / ext / size / date
    Ctrl-F5 ......... cycle column: size / date / time / attributes
    Ctrl-F6 ......... incremental quick-search
    Ctrl-F7/F8 ...... tag / untag files by *.mask
    Panel footer .... shows "<n> Files <free>K free"; once you tag files it
                      shows "<n> selected  <total> bytes" instead. The clock
                      (command row, right) ticks once a second on its own.
    Ctrl-A .......... edit file attributes (Read-only/Hidden/System/Archive)
    Ctrl-F9 ......... list archive contents (CCZIP)
    Ctrl-F10 ........ toggle the panel body between the full list and a brief
                      3-column names-only view. In brief view Left/Right move
                      between columns (they page in the full view).

  DISPLAY (cont.)
    Long names ...... the cursor file's long name shows on the command row
                      when an LFN provider is active (Win9x DOS / DOSLFN);
                      on plain DOS the 8.3 name is used.

  EXTERNAL TOOLS (type the name at the prompt, then Enter)
    CCHEX <file> .... hex + ASCII dump of any file (binary viewer)
    CCSUM <file> .... CRC-32 + byte size (verify two files match)
    CCGREP w d m .... search file contents (also Alt-F8)
    CCFIND p d ...... find files by name (also Alt-F7)
    CCZIP <zip> ..... list a ZIP archive (also Ctrl-F9)
    CCDIFF f1 f2 .... byte-compare two files (offset of first difference)
    CCSPLIT f n[K] .. split a file into f.001, f.002, ... of n bytes each
    CCJOIN out base . rejoin base.001, base.002, ... into one file
    CCREN src dst ... wildcard multi-rename, e.g. CCREN *.TXT *.BAK

  CONFIG
    cc.ini .......... set initial "sort" and "columns" options
    cc.lng .......... translate the F-key bar (copy da.lng to cc.lng)

  Scroll this help with Up/Down/PgUp/PgDn; press Esc, q, F1 or F10 to close.
